7.27pm Out come the players, with Travis Head and Abhishek Sharma leading the line for SRH. Looks like Lockie Ferguson will take the first ball ... no, it'll be the spin of Will Jacks. Right into the action from the outset.

7.15pm Right, what do we have in store tonight? RCB desperately need to get their campaign heading in the right direction, and at least by bowling first, they spare themselves the angst of working out what is a competitive total. That said, SRH haven't been guilty of second-guessing their approach too often this year. And on a small ground like the Chinnaswammy, who knows what heights they could attain...

RCB have the worst economy rate and fewest wickets in powerplays this IPL while Sunrisers are the joint second-quickest batting team in powerplays this season. That could decide what's in store early on.

Karthik: "Am I reading it right? RCB are bowling first but they named only 4 bowlers and left Siraj out yet named as impact sub. Sometimes this impact rules confuses me." Have to admit, it permanently confuses me!

Royal Challengers Bengaluru XI: F. du Plessis(c), V. Kohli, W. Jacks, R. Patidar, S. Chauhan, D. Karthik(w), M. Lomror, R. Topley, L. Ferguson, V. Vyshak, Y. Dayal. Impact options: S Prabhudessai, A Rawat, Swapnil Singh, M Siraj, Karn Sharma

Sunrisers Hyderabad XI: T Head, A Sharma, A Markram, H Klaasen(wk), A Samad, N Reddy, S Ahmed, P Cummins(c), B Kumar, J Unadkat, T Natarajan. Impact options: U Malik, Anmolpreet Singh, M Markande, G Phillips, R Tripathi

Toss: RCB win the toss and opt to bowl.

du Plessis: [The pitch has been] pretty much the same. Playing a little bit two-paced and slower than expected. That's the nature of the game and we need to play what's in front. We haven't played our best cricket, we're not delivering to our skill and some of the guys aren't playing their best. Maxwell is sitting out and so is Siraj. Ferguson is coming in.

Looks like Chauhan has come into the starting XI as the second change.

Cummins: We're going with the same team. 240 feels like par at Chinnaswamy.

Toss coming up in a few minutes and we will have Ian Bishop on our live show. Don't go anywhere!

6.50pm This ground is known as a batters' paradise but somehow this season hasn't quite provided the big scores. Three games so far and the highest score has been KKR's 186. It seems like the Chinnaswamy tracks have been turning and gripping a bit more than usual. RCB can't even boast of a big-name spinner in their ranks to try and stop the SRH fireworks before Klaasen, learning from how Mumbai Indians used Nabi's offspin last night before Shivam Dube came out to bat. Can the RCB line-up step up tonight? They'll be hoping Siraj turns his form around, at least.

Prateek: "Topley and Ferguson both is exactly what RCB needs. Their batting line up looks good enough, but bowlers need to step up. Time for Siraj to find what works for him in T20s as he is a contender for WC squad as well."

Rahim Chagani: "RCB's issue is their middle/lower order, particularly when the top order fails. They can't always rely on DK to bail them out. In comparison, SRH have Klaasen, Samad, Shabhaz and Cummins lower down their order. They can all clear the fence from the first ball. It's relentless. "

Hemant Brar has waded through the Monday traffic and made it to the ground. He says: "Ferguson has marked his run-up and Topley too. I am not able to spot Maxwell, maybe they are going in with Faf, Jacks, Lockie and Topley as their four overseas." Update: Maxwell is also there.

Cricfan: "If indeed they are going with both Topley and Lockie, then it is a good move. Their main problem is bowling. I hope Siraj also gets a break for a few games, and he can come back refreshed. One more thing RCB is losing out on, is the lack of left-right combinations. That is easily costing around 15-20 runs in my opinion. It will be good if the playing XII is -- Faf, Kohli, Jacks, Saurav, Patidar, Lomror, DK, Himanshu, Vyshak, Yash, Topley, Lockie. Impact players swap will be Patidar and Yash. "

What all can we expect in this game? Here's Abhimanyu's preview.

6.30 Hello, hello! We're back at the Chinnaswamy in Luru after nearly two weeks and boy, don't RCB need some home advantage. But it's just one home game for them before they fly to Kolkata and tonight they're against an in-form Sunrisers Hyderabad. A bowling attack under fire against a batting line-up on fire. The home team languishing at the bottom against the visitors placed fourth right now. A team with four losses in a row to take on a team with back-to-back wins in two games. Greetings to one and all, this is match 30 and we'll bring you the toss in 30.

This can for example be used to adapt the order in which content is shown to you, so that it is even easier for you to find (non-advertising) content that matches your interests.

  • Measure advertising performance 744 partners can use this purpose

    Information regarding which advertising is presented to you and how you interact with it can be used to determine how well an advert has worked for you or other users and whether the goals of the advertising were reached. For instance, whether you saw an ad, whether you clicked on it, whether it led you to buy a product or visit a website, etc. This is very helpful to understand the relevance of advertising campaigns.

  • Measure content performance 371 partners can use this purpose

    Information regarding which content is presented to you and how you interact with it can be used to determine whether the (non-advertising) content e.g. reached its intended audience and matched your interests. For instance, whether you read an article, watch a video, listen to a podcast or look at a product description, how long you spent on this service and the web pages you visit etc. This is very helpful to understand the relevance of (non-advertising) content that is shown to you.

  • Understand audiences through statistics or combinations of data from different sources 467 partners can use this purpose

    Reports can be generated based on the combination of data sets (like user profiles, statistics, market research, analytics data) regarding your interactions and those of other users with advertising or (non-advertising) content to identify common characteristics (for instance, to determine which target audiences are more receptive to an ad campaign or to certain contents).

  • Develop and improve services 560 partners can use this purpose

    Information about your activity on this service, such as your interaction with ads or content, can be very helpful to improve products and services and to build new products and services based on user interactions, the type of audience, etc. This specific purpose does not include the development or improvement of user profiles and identifiers.

  • Use limited data to select content 136 partners can use this purpose

    Content presented to you on this service can be based on limited data, such as the website or app you are using, your non-precise location, your device type, or which content you are (or have been) interacting with (for example, to limit the number of times a video or an article is presented to you).
